overview.longBusinessSummary: National Vision Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiaries, operates as an optical retailer in the United States. It operates in two segments, Owned & Host and Legacy. The company offers eyeglasses and contact lenses, and optical accessory products; provides eye exams through its America's Best, Eyeglass World, Vista Optical, Fred Meyer, Vista Optical military, Discount Contacts, and Walmart Vision Center stores. It also offers health maintenance organization and optometric services. The company was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Duluth, Georgia.
